    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Light armor made from quilted cotton cloth in postclassic central Mexico. Typically a type of sleeveless vest worn on the upper body that was particularly effective protection from arrow strikes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Armadura ligera hecha de tela de algodón acolchada en el México central posclásico. Por lo general, se trata de un tipo de chaleco sin mangas que se llevaba en la parte superior del cuerpo y que era una protección especialmente eficaz contra los golpes de flecha.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109721/GRI, FloCo terminology (2019-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ce tlamantli tlen ica momanahuiah, acazotic, tlachihualli ica yoyomitl tlen ichcatl tzotzoltic pan Mexco central posclásico. Zaniloa ica ce tlamantli cotomitl (chaleco) tlen axquipiya imancax tlen mohuicayaya ica iixco tlacayoliztli huan ni eliyaya ce tlapalehuiliztli, tlahuel quinpalehuiyaya quemman quinmahcahuiliyayah flechaz.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Eastern Huasteca Nahuatl</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000320/GRI-FloCo</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
